<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="348" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="69.[2072,2666,2110,2532]" pageId="69" pageNumber="348">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehmann" authorityYear="1961" box="[2074,2347,2224,2257]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycercus">Microtus brachycercus</taxonomicName>
is in subgenus Terricola and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1838" box="[2140,2201,2267,2296]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Pitymys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">savii</taxonomicName>
species group. It was previously synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1838" box="[2335,2444,2303,2336]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Pitymys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="69" pageNumber="347" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">M. savii</taxonomicName>
but elevated to a separate species based on chromosomal and molecular evidence. Hybrid males from experimental crosses between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1838" box="[2605,2666,2425,2454]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Pitymys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">savii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehmann" authorityYear="1961" box="[2136,2290,2460,2493]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachycercus">brachycercus</taxonomicName>
are sterile. It was classified in genus 
<taxonomicName box="[2201,2298,2499,2532]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Pitymys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pitymys</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1460,1735,2538,2571]" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6760663" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6760663" box="[1460,1735,2538,2571]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6760663/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" startId="69.[1460,1632,2538,2571]" targetBox="[1457,2049,2117,2531]" targetPageId="69">
