<emphasis bold="true" box="[1459,1594,2972,3005]" pageId="69" pageNumber="348">Breeding.</emphasis>
Female Calabria Pine Voles collected in March from Monte Gargano (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[1472,1566,3015,3044]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apulia</taxonomicName>
) had 2—4 embryos (mean 3-4).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
